description: More from NPR Music: Tiny Desk Concerts: https://www.npr.org/tinydesk‚ÄãTwitter: https://twitter.com/nprmusic‚ÄãInstagram: https://www.instagram.com/nprmusicMore from Justin Bieber:Peaches Video: https://justinbieber.lnk.to/PeachesVidJustice The Album Out Now: https://justinbieber.lnk.to/Justice  The Tiny Desk is working from home for the foreseeable future. Introducing NPR Music's Tiny Desk (home) concerts, bringing you performances from across the country and the world. It's the same spirit ‚Äî stripped-down sets, an intimate setting ‚Äî just a different space.Stephen Thompson | March 17, 2021If you were to apply one of those how it started / how it's going memes to Tiny Desk (home) concerts ‚Äî which began, it turns out, almost exactly one year ago ‚Äî you'd have, under how it's going, the image of pop superstar Justin Bieber as he and his band perform the world premiere of a new song called Peaches.Peaches will exist in a significantly different form when Bieber drops his new album Justice on Friday ‚Äî the track will feature guest vocals from GIVE≈åN and Daniel Caesar ‚Äî just as Holy, another song from Justice, opens this set without the presence of guest Chance the Rapper. But Bieber's Tiny Desk set, performed with the aid of We the Band, provides the fullest taste yet (fully 25 percent!) of the singer's sixth album, whose singles have already been streamed hundreds of millions of times.Bieber has had a massive month as he prepares for Justice to drop: March 2021 began with the singer's 27th birthday and recently produced his second career Grammy, as he took the prize for best country duo or group performance for 10,000 Hours with Dan + Shay. It continues with this, his Tiny Desk debut. description: want to get the famous 11 line abs? good, let's train our entire core ‚ô•Ô∏é  / Werbung We (hopefully) all know: you will not magically get ab lines & lose all your belly fat by doing 5 crunches. I wish it was that easy haha. But let's make sure our lines are readyyyy below the soft pillows. Being well prepared is always beneficial, we are ready for the moment we get to see those muscles. To see, ab lines you need to: ‚ñ∏ have strong ab muscles. Especially obliques (the sides), but also upper, lower and middle abs. It's basically only possible with a combination out of all areas. Think about runway models: they are often super duper skinny but don't have visible abs. So yes, we all have abs - but IT IS a matter of training them & making them pop out.‚ñ∏ have low body fat storages at your core. Everybody stores weight at different areas, so some people don't even need to have a super low body fat percentage to see those lines! If you naturally store more fat around your stomach though, you will need to be more shredded.  ‚ñ∏ sleep well & don't stress so much: why? Stress increases the hormone cortisol, which supports fat storages around your belly. title: Golden Retriever snaps at groomer
tags: [none]
description: Brooke's is a young dog who is just learning about life. Important to note holding by the muzzle is common practice for a groomer while trimming the face and head. I am not applying any pressure, or causing him any pain. Most dogs will give me warning signals before attempting to bite. In this situation I had no warning, and that's what makes this so unexpected, especially coming from a Golden Retriever. The dog has also been groomed elsewhere, so it is possible a groomer may have held him too tightly by the muzzle and he remembered that.The owner was informed and sent home with homework to get the dog comfortable about having his face touched. We must touch the muzzle in order to wash and towel it dry, so the dog needs to be compliant for that.
